The course gives an overview of basic methods for prevention of social problems of pupils and for intervention in the case these problems emerge at individual, group and school level.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give students methodological principles for prevention and intervention of pupils' social problems with pedagogical means.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completing the course a student will be able to: - demonstrate understanding of mean methots of social pedagogy in educational context; - evaluate, analyze and have a willingness to apply different prevention and intervention strategies in individual, group and whole school level originated from socialpedagogical viewpoint.
